						               													<description>Take Care of Polar Bears is an environment friendly serious game. It offers an opportunity to experience the ecological crisis of Polar Bears indirectly. It gives you the educational values as well, which means that can help to not only understand the causes of climate change problems better, but also know how to deal with them by role-playing in this game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This board game is played by using cards, not dices basically and the board can be made up with 17 glaciers tiles arbitrarily. There are 54 cards including moving cards, recharging cards, and hunter cards, etc. Players can have three cards in their hands and they use one of their cards in each turn. By using these cards efficiently, the player who reaches the finish tile at first will be a winner. This board game can be used in anywhere, for example, schools, cultural organizations, business training, when someone needs an education about environments or ecological values.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
